</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1332,1932]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1872,1896]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has unique coloration of the pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[956,1027,1871,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1786,1809]" captionTargetBox="[198,1413,221,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[169,1417,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 5. Species of Agalliini. A, E, I, Purvigallia maculata gen. et sp. nov. B, F, J, Sinoagallia serrata gen. et sp. nov.; C, G, K, Sungallia truncata gen. et sp. nov.; D, H, L, Skandagallia dietrichi gen. et sp. nov. [A – D. Habitus, dorsal view; E – H. Habitus, lateral view; I – L. Face]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215161/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[1014,1027,1871,1895]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A) and has paired ventral preatrial processes and the caudal lobe of the pygofer narrowed and prolonged caudodorsally.
</paragraph>
